u}(	ext{para-nitroacetophenone}) > 	ilde{
u}(	ext{benzophenone})$ because the methyl group provides minimal conjugation to the carbonyl, maximizing the carbonyl bond strength, whereas the para-nitro group introduces additional conjugation pathways that delocalize and weaken the carbonyl more than in acetophenone.

D. $	ilde{
