u}(	ext{benzophenone}) > 	ilde{
u}(	ext{acetophenone})$ because the increased mass of aryl substitution lowers the reduced mass in the carbonyl stretching coordinate and dominates over conjugative effects, raising the frequency relative to acetophenone, while the para-nitro effect is largely remote and negligible on the carbonyl.
